snippet.textDisplay:
France, Canada, and Australia fighting Google and Facebook for news link taxes? Spain has something to tell you about that. 

You want to be hosted on the most popular places to see news for free. Hell you're lucky they don't charge you to be hosted. Your click through traffic is paying you for the ads you put on your news pages! Do you not understand? Spain's news agencies tanked when Google just pulled out after a similar law passed. Now it's way harder to get people to their sites. Sure they "won" but then they lost literally millions by losing the non subscribers who won't ever find their stories now. The data supports it being a bad idea to try to tax Google for the privilege to be on their servers.
